Names: Franky Irazaba and Brandon Montalvo

Build Instructions:
Run `make` to build the shell executable `slosh`.

Run Instructions:
Run `./slosh` to start the shell.

Special Instructions / Notes:
- This shell supports execution of external commands, built-in commands (`cd`, `exit`), pipes (`|`), and output redirection (`>` and `>>`).
- Output redirection is assumed to appear at the end of a command or at the end of a pipeline.
- Multiple output redirections in a single command line are not supported.
- Redirection is applied only to the final command in a pipeline.
- This implementation does not support quoted arguments or advanced shell syntax beyond the assignment requirements.
- SIGINT handling is implemented so that Ctrl-C does not terminate the shell, but does terminate foreground child processes.